Program: Outlook
Title: How hunting a murderer nearly killed me
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csz37h
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 7 Jul 2019
Former FBI agent John E. Douglas is an expert on serial killers. He spent years interviewing imprisoned murderers to try to understand their psychology. Through that he hoped he'd be able to help police officers solve crimes. But the gruelling work took its toll on John. Andrea Kennedy spoke to him about how his mental health began to crumble and very nearly cost him his life. Image: John E. Douglas Credit: Alexander James Towle/Fairfax Media via Getty Images Show less